Manaburn needs time.<br>
<br>
Once the ranger had the AA points, the Bow, the group, etc.. They can keep taking down mob, after mob.. <br>
<br>
The Wizards get one shot.. Then they have to wait for sometime. <br>
<br>
Yes, most dragons are on long spawn timers, but not all mobs are..<br>
<br>
The idea that Wizards ARE finally where they should be is pretty much the only reason I am sticking around this game. <br>
<br>
So if VI wants to lose one more player to the Host of other games out there.. Nerf Wizards again. I had to deal with the other Nerfs, and that's why I quit playing the Wizard before and Started Melee again - Now that I can play a Wizard that really can do what a Wizard should be able to do.. It seems VI might nerf again.. I hope this isn't an indication of EQ2.. Nerf, after Nerf for casters, while they add Insane Weapons with crazy Ratios and Regen/Resist gear for tanks out the ass..<br>
<br>
Ok, so the Wizards can finally do something no other class can, collectively.. Hmm, seems they might actually have a use now beyond a porter.. Hmm, better Nerf them! But be sure to leave in the Ranger Damage.. That's balancing.<br>
<br>
Sorry, there's no reason a lvl 60 Wizard shouldn't be able to fry the hell outta some mobs.. It's why we play Wizards!!<br>
